Configuration Directives
Directive is an instruction that tells apache what to do

-One per line
-Instruction telling Apache what to do
-Usually followed by an argument

 	Data passed to the directive
 	Example: ServerName - Sets hostname, port for redirects
 	ServerName www.example.com

 -Case-insensitive
	 ServerName == servername
 	 Some arguments are case-sensitive
     Best practice: treat all as case-sensitive



 Commands

 $cat  /etc/apache2/apache2.conf | less
 
-Link 
https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/directives.html
https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/core.html#documentroot



Search recursively (-R) and case insenstive (-i)

$cd /etc/apache2$ grep -Ri DocumentRoot .

$less /etc/apache2/srv/web/index.html

HTTP_ROOT
apache configuration files are stored i.e 
/etc/apache2

DocumentRoot 
/srv/web


